interests include health inequality, immigrant adaptation, gender, social capital, and quantitative methods.
In her doctoral dissertation, she conducted an empirical analysis using longitudinal data on multicultural
adolescents in Korea to examine patterns of social capital at the individual and family levels and their
relationship to health disparities. She has presented her research at domestic and international academic
conferences, including the Korean Sociological Association, the Korean Population Association, and
ANPOR-APCA. Her work has been published in SSCI journals such as the International Journal of Intercultural
Relations, Cross- Cultural Research, and Applied Research in Quality of Life. She holds a BA, MA, and PhD
