Chinese economic policy. Recognizing the limitations of state and capital centered perspectives in
addressing lived social realities, she returned to Ewha Womans University to pursue an integrated M.S./Ph.D.
in Social Welfare. She is interested in the dual mechanisms of social capital and its role in both
exacerbating inequality and enabling policy intervention, with an emphasis on welfare policy design and
public welfare attitudes when implementing policies.`,
      links: [{ label: 'Email', href: 'mailto:shl25@yonsei.ac.kr' }],
    },
  ],

  graduateStudents: [
    {
      name: 'Kiho Sung',
      title: undefined,
