Sociology. Her primary research interests include neuroscience and crime sociology. Specifically, she is
interested in how post-victimization processing and acceptance of criminal experiences may relate to
differences in neural activation patterns and variations in social network structure. Her research explores
brain-computer interfacing and network-based approaches to crime, victimization, and neuro-social activation
mechanisms.`,
      links: [{ label: 'Email', href: 'mailto:chaeeunkim088@gmail.com' }],
    },
    {
      name: 'Hyunseo Yoon',
      title: undefined,
      metaLines: [],
      image: '/team/und_yun.jpg',
      bio: `Hyunseo Yoon is a second-year undergraduate researcher in Sociology at Yonsei University. Her primary
research interests lie in quantitative social analysis of social networks. She is primarily committed to
transforming social structures into measurable and visualizable data to examine structural conditions and
its process in shaping individual and collective outcomes. On a broader surface, she is interested in
identifying structural sources of social problems and contributing to evidence-informed solutions.
Currently, she is exploring multiple subfields of sociology, including social institutions, medical
sociology, urban sociology.`,
      links: [],
    },
  ],
